We have an opening at the Vitro Glass Technology Center in Cheswick, PA for a R&D Computer Programmer! 
This position in the Vacuum Coatings Process group will support research and technical programs aimed at developing new products and process improvements for thin film coatings on glass for architectural and automotive applications. This position will also support existing software and develop new software for quality control of thin film coating production. Production support will include daily trouble-shooting and maintenance of quality control systems to sustain high-volume coated glass production at Vitroâ€™s installed base of vacuum coaters in the United States and Mexico. 
Key Roles and Responsibilities: 
Support and develop computer programs for optical modelling equipment, quality control equipment, and sheet resistance measurement systems 
Daily trouble-shooting and improvement of computer programs used to control and measure properties of low emissivity thin film coatings 
Compile research reports and communicate scientific/engineering findings in meetings to the audience from diverse background 
~25%-35% time of travel will be required for project launch and execution 
During travel and working at plants, overtime and weekend/evening hours are sometimes needed 
 
 
 Job Requirements 
 BS Electrical, Mechanical, Chemical, Physics, Computer Science, or another science or engineering degree; MS preferred 
Coding skills in at least two programming languages such as Visual Basic, C, C++, C#, VB, MATLAB, Python, etc. 
Excellent listening skills and communication skills, particularly with manufacturing personnel and equipment operators 
Able to display complex technical information and communicate clearly and simply to people who may not have much background in a technical area 
Fundamental understanding of statistics and process engineering 
Highly driven and self-motivated to continually learn and expand skill sets 
Strong sense of ownership and dedication to timely and detailed follow-through 
Good interpersonal communication and writing skills 
A dditional preferred: 
Knowledge of flat glass and vacuum coating manufacturing processes 
Familiarity with concepts of color measurement, thin film characterization, thin film optics, and vacuum coating equipment 
Experience with operating and maintaining electrical/mechanical scientific instruments 
Technical knowledge and experience in Wonderware InTouch, Allen Bradley PLC, and/or other types of control systems 
Experience with SQL, OSISoft-PI, and Azure Platform and familiarity with artificial intelligence and machine learning concepts and implementation Vitro 1 day ago original job Report job Apply Now Apply On Company Site Save this job Save this job Computer Programmer jobs in Cheswick, PA Jobs at Vitro in Cheswick, PA Computer Programmer salaries in Cheswick, PA Company Info Follow Get job updates from Vitro Vitro 794 reviews With more than 14,000 employees worldwide, Vitro is one of the worldâ€™s leading glass manufacturers, and the largest in the Western Hemisp... Let employers find you Thousands of employers search for candidates on Indeed Upload your resume Hiring Lab Career Advice Browse Jobs Browse Companies Salaries Find Certifications Indeed Events Work at Indeed Countries About Help Center Â© 2021 Indeed Do Not Sell My Personal Information Accessibility at Indeed Privacy Center Cookies Privacy Terms Let Employers Find You Upload Your Resume 
 
 
 
 
 
